 :tx/rationale "UAQ CRITICAL REVISION: COST-AWARE ACQUISITION FUNCTION. The current UAQ tasks (v2) use product composition: A = impact * relevance * novelty * confidence. The ORIGINAL ADR-FOUNDATION-019 (Session 034) specifies: alpha(action|store) = E[delta_F(S)] / cost(action). This is fundamentally better. ANALYSIS: (1) Product composition picks the highest absolute expected value. Cost-aware composition picks the highest VALUE PER UNIT COST. (2) For context blocks: cost = token count. alpha = E[delta_F(S)] / tokens. This naturally optimizes token efficiency — the Markov blanket maximizes information transfer per token. A 10-token block with 0.005 expected improvement (alpha=0.0005) outranks a 100-token block with 0.01 improvement (alpha=0.0001). (3) For tasks: cost = wall_time estimate. alpha = E[delta_F(S)] / time. This is ROI — maximize improvement per unit time. (4) For ceremony: cost = ceremony_tokens. alpha = E[improved_M(t)] / methodology_cost. (5) The product formula becomes HOW we compute E[delta_F(S)]: expected_delta_fs = impact * relevance * novelty * confidence. Then alpha = expected_delta_fs / cost. Both formulas coexist — product computes the numerator, division by cost produces the ranking. IMPACT: UAQ-1 must include ObservationCost struct and ObservationKind enum (8 kinds from ADR-019, start with 3). AcquisitionScore needs expected_delta_fs, cost, and alpha fields. Ranking by alpha not composite. ORIGINAL 8 KINDS: Task, Extraction, Review, WitnessRefresh, BoundaryCheck, CouplingExploration, CalibrationMeasurement, AnomalyInvestigation. Start with 3 (Task, Block, Boundary), rest are Phase E extensibility."
